JOHNSON vs. BOARD OF CANVASSERS (Casnovia), No. 14174, 101 M., 187.

(Certiorari to Kent.)

To compel a rfe-count of tbe votes cast at a village election ■and to declare tbe result. Tbe circuit judge gxranted tbe writ.

Reversed June 16, 1894, with costs.

Held, that Act. Ho. 208, Laws of '1887, does not cover village elections.
